1B. POLYMORPHISM — CORE THEORY
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  [T][ ] What are the 4 pillars of OOP? Explain each with a real-world example.
         (Encapsulation, Inheritance, Polymorphism, Abstraction)
         Asked at: TCS, Wipro, Infosys, Zoho, Amazon, Microsoft

  [T][ ] What is polymorphism? What are its two types in C++?
         (Compile-time/Static: overloading; Runtime/Dynamic: virtual functions)
         Asked at: TCS, Wipro, Infosys, Zoho, Amazon

  [T][ ] What is the difference between function overloading and function overriding?
         (Overloading: same name, different params, same class;
          Overriding: same signature, different class, virtual keyword)
         Asked at: TCS, Wipro, Infosys, Zoho, Amazon

  [T][ ] What is the difference between overloading, overriding, and hiding?
         Give an example of function hiding.
         Asked at: TCS, Zoho, Persistent, L&T Infotech

  [T][ ] What is a virtual function? Why do we need it?
         Asked at: TCS, Wipro, Amazon, Zoho, L&T Infotech

  [T][ ] What is early binding vs late binding (static vs dynamic dispatch)?
         Asked at: TCS, Wipro, Infosys, Amazon, Microsoft

  [T][ ] What is a vtable (virtual function table)? How does it work?
         Asked at: TCS, Wipro, Amazon, Samsung, Zoho

  [T][ ] Explain the vtable and vptr mechanism in detail.
         (Each class with virtual functions has a vtable; each object has a vptr pointing to it)
         Asked at: Amazon, Samsung, Sasken, embedded C++ roles

  [T][ ] What is the overhead of a virtual function call vs a direct call?
         Asked at: Dolat Capital, HFT firms, Sasken

  [T][ ] What is devirtualization? When can the compiler perform it?
         Asked at: Dolat Capital, HFT firms

  [T][ ] What is a virtual destructor? Why is it important?
         (Without it: deleting derived via base pointer causes undefined behavior / memory leak)
         Asked at: Amazon, Microsoft, Google, TCS, Wipro, Adobe

  [T][ ] Can constructors be virtual? Can destructors be virtual?
         (Constructors: No. Destructors: Yes — and base destructor SHOULD be virtual)
         Asked at: Amazon, TCS, Wipro, Infosys

  [T][ ] Can you call a virtual function from a constructor or destructor? What happens?
         (It calls the base class version — vtable not yet pointing to derived)
         Asked at: Amazon, Microsoft, Adobe

  [T][ ] Can you call a non-virtual function polymorphically? Explain.
         (No — non-virtual uses static binding based on pointer type, not actual object type)
         Asked at: Zoho, Persistent

  [T][ ] What is the difference between the override and final keywords?
         (override: forces derived to override; final: prevents further overriding)
         Asked at: Persistent, Nagarro, L&T Infotech

  [T][ ] What is operator overloading? Which operators cannot be overloaded?
         (Cannot overload: :: . .* ?: sizeof typeid)
         Asked at: TCS, Wipro, Zoho, Samsung, Adobe

  [T][ ] What is a covariant return type? Give an example.
         (Derived override can return a pointer/reference to derived type instead of base type)
         Asked at: Advanced C++ roles, Google

  [T][ ] What is CRTP (Curiously Recurring Template Pattern)?
         How does it achieve static polymorphism?
         Asked at: Dolat Capital, HFT firms, Advanced C++ roles

  ★[T][ ] What is the difference between static polymorphism and dynamic polymorphism?
         Give a performance comparison.
         (Static: templates/overloading, resolved at compile-time, zero overhead;
          Dynamic: vtable/vptr, resolved at runtime, indirect call overhead)
         Asked at: Google, Dolat Capital, Goldman Sachs, HFT firms

  ★[T][ ] Can a virtual function be inline? Is it ever inlined by the compiler?
         (Declared inline but usually not inlined when called via pointer/reference)
         Asked at: Samsung, L&T Infotech, Persistent

  ★[T][ ] What is the difference between compile-time and runtime polymorphism
         from a memory/performance perspective?
         Asked at: Amazon, Samsung, Sasken

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1C. ABSTRACTION — CORE THEORY
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  [T][ ] What is a pure virtual function? What is an abstract class?
         (Pure virtual: virtual void f() = 0; Abstract: has at least one pure virtual)
         Asked at: TCS, Wipro, Amazon, Zoho, Infosys

  [T][ ] What is a pure virtual function? Can it have a body?
         (Yes — pure virtual CAN have a body, it just forces override in derived)
         Asked at: Amazon, Microsoft, Persistent

  [T][ ] What is an abstract class? Can you instantiate it?
         (No — must be subclassed with all pure virtuals overridden)
         Asked at: TCS, Wipro, Infosys, Amazon

  [T][ ] What is an interface in C++? How do you implement it?
         (Abstract class with ALL pure virtual functions and no data members)
         Asked at: Amazon, Microsoft, TCS

  [T][ ] What is encapsulation? Why is it important?
         Asked at: TCS, Wipro, Infosys, Zoho, Amazon

  [T][ ] What is the difference between public, private, and protected access specifiers?
         Asked at: TCS, Wipro, Infosys, Zoho

  [T][ ] What is object slicing? When does it happen? How do you prevent it?
         (Passing derived by value to base type — extra members get sliced off)
         (Prevent: use pointer or reference to base)
         Asked at: Amazon, Microsoft, Zoho, Persistent

  [T][ ] What is RTTI (Run Time Type Information)?
         (dynamic_cast, typeid — enables type queries at runtime)
         Asked at: Amazon, Microsoft, Adobe

  [T][ ] What is the difference between dynamic_cast and static_cast?
         (dynamic_cast: runtime check, safe downcast; static_cast: compile-time, no runtime check)
         Asked at: Amazon, Microsoft, Adobe, Persistent

  [T][ ] What is the difference between struct and class in C++?
         (Only difference: struct defaults to public access, class defaults to private)
         Asked at: TCS, Wipro, Infosys (very common)

  [T][ ] What does the explicit keyword do in constructors?
         (Prevents implicit/automatic conversions)
         Asked at: Amazon, Adobe, Persistent, Nagarro

  [T][ ] What is a mutable member? When would you use it?
         (Can be modified even in a const method — e.g. caching, logging)
         Asked at: Amazon, Adobe, advanced C++ roles

  [T][ ] What is a friend function? When would you use it?
         Asked at: TCS, Wipro, Infosys, Zoho

  [T][ ] What is the 'this' pointer? Give an example of when you would use it.
         Asked at: TCS, Wipro, Infosys, Amazon

  ★[T][ ] What is the Open/Closed Principle (OCP)?
         How does abstraction and polymorphism enable it?
         Asked at: Amazon, Google, Atlassian, Adobe

  ★[T][ ] When should you use an abstract class vs a pure interface in C++?
         (Abstract class: shared default behavior + interface;
          Interface: only contract, no state)
         Asked at: Amazon, Microsoft, Adobe, Atlassian

